dc_title_s: Taylor County, Iowa, 1936, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol DB form of individual image numbering: DB-1-[number], DB-2-[number], DB-3-[number], DB-4-[number], DB-5-[number], or DB-7-[number]. Date of publication inferred from dates on individual photographs within the mosaic. Flown by Aerial Explorations, Inc. New York, N.Y."Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
